
[1]relation

   RELA'TION, n. [L. relatio, refero.]

   1. The act of telling; recital; account; narration; narrative of facts;
   as a historical relation. We listened to the relation of his
   adventures.

   2. Respect; reference; regard.

   I have been importuned to make some observations on this art, in
   relation to its agreement with poetry.

   3. Connection between things; mutual respect, or what one thing is with
   regard to another; as the relation of a citizen to the state; the
   relation of a subject to the supreme authority; the relation of husband
   and wife, or of master and servant; the relation of a state of
   probation to a state of retribution.

   4. Kindred; alliance; as the relation of parents and children.

   Relations dear, and all the charities of father, son and brother, first
   were known.

   5. A person connected by consanguinity or affinity; a kinsman or
   kinswoman. He passed a month with his relations in the country.

   6. Resemblance of phenomena; analogy.

   7. In geometry, ratio; proportion.
